The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 3: Just a day after the government?s decision to hike the FDI limit in telecom from 49 per cent to 74 per cent, Aircel Televentures Ltd has reportedly decided to sell a 49 per cent stake in Russia?s AFK Sistema for $450 million. Aircel Televentures is the holding company of Aircel Ltd and Aircel Cellular Ltd, which have licences to provide cellular mobile services in 12 of India?s 23 telecom circles.

 New Delhi, Feb. 3: Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Ltd today said it will consider issuing over 5 crore bonus shares in the ratio of 1:1 subject to approval by shareholders. Glenmark has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange that it would seek the approval through a postal ballot.

 New Delhi, Feb. 3: Commerce minister Kamal Nath today said the next mini-ministerial of G-20 nations to discuss agriculture-related issues for the WTO will be held here on March 18 and 19.

 New Delhi, Feb. 3: Aviva life Insurance, the private insurer, today increased its capital base by Rs 77 crore, taking the total paid-up equity to Rs 320 crore. According to insurance regulations, Aviva holds a 26 per cent stake and the remaining 74 per cent is with Dabur.

 Chennai, Feb. 3: The Company Law Board, Chennai, today ordered Federal Bank to take into account ICICI Bank?s voting for its entire stake in the Kerala-based bank at the AGM held in September. As a result of the order, two ICICI Bank nominees would join the board of Federal Bank.

 New Delhi, Feb. 3: An informal group of seven public sector construction companies was constituted today to explore possibilities of strategic alliances between them. Ircon managing director B. S. Kapur has been made the convenor of the group.

 New Delhi, Feb. 3: The first ever meeting of the group of ministers on formulating an umbrella legislation for special economic zones will be held on February 11, sources said today.




